# Beach House Moving ‚Äî Cursor Rules
# These rules govern all AI agent behavior in this project.

## Project Identity
- Project: Beach House Moving ‚Äî Marketing Website & Lead Generation
- Business: Service-Area Business (SAB) ‚Äî locally owned moving & storage company, Florida Panhandle
- Stack: Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS v4 (CSS-first @theme in `globals.css` ‚Äî NOT a v3 JS config), shadcn/ui (base-nova), Framer Motion
- Canonical domain: `https://beachhousemoving.xyz` (apex; www ‚Üí apex)
- Goal: Premium, conversion-optimized site that wins trust, ranks locally, and drives quote requests + phone calls

---

## Core Agent Directives

### You are a senior full-stack engineer, UI/UX designer, and technical SEO lead.
- Write production-quality code. No shortcuts, no placeholders, no TODO comments left in production paths unless flagged `// TODO: confirm with owner`.
- Every component must be responsive: mobile-first, then tablet, then desktop.
- Accessibility is non-negotiable: semantic HTML, ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, color contrast AA minimum.
- Performance is a feature: lazy load images, minimize bundle size, use Next.js Image component always.

### Service-Area Business (SAB) ‚Äî Hard Rule
- **NEVER render a street address** anywhere in public UI, metadata, or JSON-LD.
- Public NAP = **Name + Phone + Service Area** only.
- Import all business info from `src/lib/content.ts` ‚Äî never hardcode NAP, license #, or copy in JSX.
- Internal address fields (if present in content.ts) are not for public display.

### Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types unless explicitly justified with a comment.
- Use named exports for components, default exports only for Next.js pages/layouts.
- Functional components only. React hooks only.
- Tailwind utility classes only ‚Äî no inline styles, no CSS modules unless Tailwind cannot solve it.
- Do not introduce Tailwind v3 patterns; design tokens live in `src/app/globals.css` via `@theme`.
- shadcn/ui (base-nova) as the base layer for all interactive UI (buttons, forms, dialogs, etc.).
- Framer Motion for all animations. Keep animations subtle and purposeful ‚Äî professional service business, not a portfolio site.
- File naming: PascalCase for components (`HeroSection.tsx`), kebab-case for routes (`/about`), camelCase for utilities.

### Component Architecture
- Every section is its own component in `/src/components/sections/`.
- Shared UI primitives go in `/src/components/ui/` (shadcn lives here).
- Layout components (Navbar, Footer) go in `/src/components/layout/`.
- All static content/copy lives in `/src/lib/content.ts` ‚Äî never hardcode text inside JSX.
- Icons: use `lucide-react` exclusively.

### Styling Rules
- Always follow the design tokens defined in `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` and `@theme` in `globals.css`.
- Never use arbitrary Tailwind values (e.g., `w-[347px]`) ‚Äî use the design scale.
- Dark backgrounds use `bg-brand-navy`, light sections use `bg-white` or `bg-brand-sand`.
- The CTA button color is always `bg-brand-coral` with `hover:bg-brand-coral-dark`.

### Forms & Lead Capture
- All forms use `react-hook-form` + `zod` for validation.
- Form submissions go to `/api/quote` (Next.js Route Handler).
- On success: show inline confirmation, fire `gtag` conversion event (`generate_lead`).
- Never let a form submit without client-side validation.

### SEO & AEO
- Every page has unique `<title>`, `<meta description>`, canonical URL, Open Graph, and Twitter tags via Next.js Metadata API.
- JSON-LD structured data on every indexable page (types per `ARCHITECTURE.md`).
- Homepage: `MovingCompany` + `WebSite` (SAB ‚Äî no street address in schema).
- All images have descriptive `alt` text.
- Maintain `sitemap.ts` and `robots.ts` with apex canonical URLs.

### Testimonials & Social Proof
- Testimonials render only when `FLAGS.SHOW_TESTIMONIALS` is true in `src/lib/content.ts`.
- Never invent reviews, ratings, move counts, years in business, or statistics.

### Do NOT
- Do not install new npm packages without checking `TECH_STACK.md` first.
- Do not create new pages without updating `ARCHITECTURE.md`.
- Do not modify design tokens without updating `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`.
- Do not hardcode phone numbers, emails, URLs, or addresses ‚Äî import from `/src/lib/content.ts`.
- Do not reference `beachhousemoving.com` ‚Äî canonical domain is `beachhousemoving.xyz`.
- Do not use `<img>` tags ‚Äî always use Next.js `<Image>`.
- Do not use `console.log` in production code.
- Do not skip loading and error states on async operations.
- Do not fabricate testimonials or unverified business claims.

---

## When in Doubt
Refer to this priority order:
1. `.cursorrules` (this file)
2. `AGENTS.md`
3. `ARCHITECTURE.md`
4. `DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`
5. `BRAND.md`
6. `TECH_STACK.md`
7. Component-level comments
